Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[Perhaps the most striking statements in this review of progress towards the global eradication of measles are: (1) that reductions in measles mortality accounted for 23% of the estimated global decline in all-cause child mortality from 1990 to 2008, and (2) that elimination of measles in the Region of the Americas had been achieved and maintained up to 2010. Unfortunately the resurgence of measles during the period 2011-2012, and the fact that by the end of 2010, 40% of countries had not met the annual incidence target of <5 cases per million, coupled with impending funding constraints, are unwelcome developments. - Mod.CP]


